HEADWORD: Decacerata
<hw>De*cac`e*ra"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>de`ka</grk> ten + <grk>ke`ras</grk> a horn.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The division of Cephalopoda which includes the
squids, cuttlefishes, and others having ten arms or tentacles; -- called
also <altname>Decapoda</altname>. <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Decacera</asp>.]</altsp> See <er>Dibranchiata</er>.</def></p>

